      "text": "In mathematics, and more specifically in [[graph theory]], a tree is an [[undirected graph]] in which any two vertices are connected by exactly one path. In other words, any acyclic connected graph is a tree. A forest is a disjoint union of trees - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_(graph_theory) wikipedia]"
